THE PRODUCT THEN POURED OUT OF THE OVER FLOW TUBES ATTACHED TO THE CONTAINMENT AREA. ESTIMATED DURATION OF RELEASE: 04:45AM TO 11:10AM. APPROXIMATELY 100-130 GALS LEAKED FROM TRAILER. TIM ODEN, MANAGER OF OUR LITTLE ROCK TERMINAL CALLED U.S.E.S. TO DO THE CLEAN UP OF THE SPILL. ANOTHER ASPHALT TRANSPORT TRUCK AND TRAILER WAS DISPATCHED TO THE SCENE TO HAVE THE CONTENTS OF THE OVERTURNED TRAILER PUMPED INTO THE 2ND TRAILER. AFTER THE TRANSFER WAS COMPLETE THE 2ND TRUCK CONTINUED TO THE ORIGINAL DESTINATION AND UNLOADED. A WRECKER SERVICE WAS CALLED TO TOW THE OVER TURNED TRUCK AND TRAILER TO OUR TERMINAL IN LITTLE ROCK ARKANSAS. U.S.E.S. CLEANED UP THE SPILLED PRODUCT AND TOOK CARE OF THE DISPOSAL OF THE WASTE. I SPOKE WITH THE MANAGER OF THE MANUFACTURER OF THE HARMON TANK TRAILER THAT WAS INVOLVED IN THE INCIDENT, MR. LOY MCGEE. HE EXPLAINED TO ME THAT THIS VENT ACCORDING TO DOT LAW MUST BE DESIGNED WITH NO MOVING PARTS. IT IS A PRESSURE VENT FOR TRAILERS HAULING ELEVATED TEMPERATURE PRODUCTS. IN OTHER WORDS IT CANNOT BE DESIGNED TO CLOSE UNDER ANY CONDITION. THE TRAILER VENT SHOULD NOT LEAK IF THE TRAILER IS UPRIGHT OR UPSIDE DOWN. AT ANY OTHER ANGLE THERE IS WAY TO STOP THIS VENT FROM LEAKING PRODUCT. THAT WAS THE EXPLANATION I GOT AFTER THE INCIDENT OCCURRED. CONTACT: HARMON TANK CO. LOY MCGEE PHONE # (806) 763-4631
column169: WE HAVE DISCUSSED THIS INCIDENT WITH THE DRIVER, AND WILL DISCUSS IN OUR FUTURE SAFETY MEETINGS WITH ALL OF OUR DRIVERS THE IMPORTANCE OF HAVING ENOUGH ROADWAY, AREA AND CLEARANCE IN ORDER TO MAKE A SAFE TURN WHILE OPERATING A SEMI TRACTOR TRAILER.

column168: DRIVER DROVE ONTO SHOULDER TO AVOID WILDLIFE AND THE PUP TRAILER LEFT ROADWAY AND OVERTUNED IN THE DITCH. THE PUP TRAILER RUPTURED AND APHALT LEAKED OUT INTO THE DITCH. WE NOTIFIED DEQ AND SENT A CLEAN UP CREW TO PICK UP THE TRAILER AND CLEAN UP THE SITE. THE SITE WAS CLEANED UP BEFORE THE END OF THE DAY 5/24.

column168: THE FOLLOWING EXPLANATION OF THE ACCIDENT ON MAY 16, 2013 HAS BEEN TAKEN FROM ACCOUNTS FROM THE DRIVER AND EMPLOYEES FROM BORK TRANSPORT OF ILLINOIS. THOMAS GEARY WHO IS AN EMPLOYEE OF AN OWNER OPERATOR OF BORK TRANSPORT WAS IN AN ACCIDENT ON INTERSTATE 80 WESTBOUND AT MILE MARKER 29 NEAR ATKINSON, ILLINOIS. MR. GEARY WAS HAULING A BULK LIQUID LOAD OF TOLUENE WHICH HE HAD PICKED UP AT CITGO IN LEMONT, ILLINOIS. MR. GEARY WAS TRANSPORTING THE LOAD OF TOLUENE TOWARD MINNESOTA MINING IN CORDOVA, ILLINOIS.  MR. GEARY DOES NOT REMEMBER WHAT CAUSED THE ACCIDENT. MR. GEARY STATES THE FIRST THING HE REMEMBERS IS BEING THROWN AROUND HIS TRUCK. HE THEN STATES HE COULD NOT GET OUT OF THE DOOR OF HIS TRUCK SO HE WENT THROUGH THE WIND SHIELD. MR. GEARY CRAWLED THROUGH THE WINDSHIELD AND STOOD NEXT TO THE TRACTOR TRYING TO BREATH. MR. GEARY THEN STATES HE HEARD SOMEONE YELL THE WORDS " DRIVER, DRIVER" AND THE PERSON CAME TO HIS AID AND REMOVED MR. GEARY AWAY FROM THE TRACTOR UNTIL EMERGENCY HELP ARRIVED. MR. GEARY STATES THIS ALL HE CAN REMEMBER. THE APPROXIMATE TIME OF THE ACCIDENT WAS 6:00 A.M. ON MAY 16, 2013.  ON MAY 16, 2013 FIRE MARSHALL FROMING CALLED BORK TRANSPORT IN SUMMIT, ILLINOIS AT APPROXIMATELY 6:20 A.M. HE STATED TO JOHN REED WHO IS A BTI EMPLOYEE THAT BTI TRAILER 5160 WAS INVOLVED IN A ROLLOVER AT MILER MARKER 29 ON I80 IN ATKINSON, ILLINOIS. JOHN REED ASKED FIRE MARSHALL FROMING WHO WAS ON THE ACCIDENT SCENE FOR HIS PHONE NUMBER AND JOHN WOULD RIGHT CALL HIM BACK. JOHN PROCEEDED TO CALL A LOCAL WRECKER (HODGES 66 IN KEWANEE, ILLINOIS). JOHN SECURED THE WRECKER TO GO TO THE ACCIDENT SIGHT. JOHN THEN DISPATCHED OWNER OPERATOR DAN JORGENSON TO TAKE A CLEAN TRAILER AND GO TO THE ACCIDENT SITE TO PUMP OUT THE TRAILER. DAN LEFT SUMMIT AROUND 7:50 A.M. AND ARRIVED AT THE ACCIDENT SITE AT 9:30 A.M. WHEN DAN ARRIVED AT THE ACCIDENT SITE THE WRECKER FROM HODGES ARRIVED.  BILL UMGELDER OF THE BTI SAFETY DEPARTMENT THEN TOOK OVER THE ACCIDENT INVESTIGATION AND ANY RISK MITIGATION IVOLVED THAT BTI MIGHT BE INVOLVED WITH IN THE ACCIDENT. MIKE TALLAKSEN WHO IS THE VICE PRESIDENT OF BTI SAFETY WENT TO THE ACCIDENT SITE TO REPRESENT BTI. BILL UMGELDER CALLED XL INSURANCE COMPANY WHO INSURES BTI. XL GROUP IS LOCATED AT 505 EAGLE VIEW BLVD., SUITE 100, EXTON, PA. THE CONTACT NAME IS CHRIS FISHER (610-968-9460).  BILL COORDINATED WITH THE XL INSURANCE COMPANY TO SEND SET ENVIRONMENTAL TO CLEAN UP ANY SPILLAGE OUT OF THE TRANSPORT. BILL ALSO MADE SURE MR. GEARY WAS TEST PER DOT REGULATIONS. BILL ALSO FILED ALL REPORTS NEEDED TO BE FILED AS NEEDED.  MIKE TALLAKSEN STAYED AT THE ACCIDENT SCENE UNTIL THE TRUCK AND TRAILER WERE REMOVED SAFELY TO HODGKINS'S. MIKE STAYED AT THE SITE FOR THE CLEANUP ALSO. THE EQUIPMENT FROM THE ACCIDENT WAS REMOVED AROUND 4:00 P.M.
